# Xcode Build Conventions

## iOS Build

Always build iOS target for **device** (not simulator):

```bash
xcodebuild -project termihui-client.xcodeproj \
  -scheme termihui-client-ios \
  -destination 'generic/platform=iOS' \
  build
```

## macOS Build

```bash
xcodebuild -project termihui-client.xcodeproj \
  -scheme termihui-client-macos \
  -destination 'platform=macOS' \
  build
```

## Running Tests

```bash
# macOS tests
xcodebuild -project termihui-client.xcodeproj \
  -scheme termihui-client-macos \
  -destination 'platform=macOS' \
  test

# iOS tests (use simulator for tests)
xcodebuild -project termihui-client.xcodeproj \
  -scheme termihui-client-ios \
  -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17' \
  test
```

## Project Structure

- `macos-client/` — Xcode project with macOS and iOS targets
- `macos-client/Shared/` — Code shared between macOS and iOS (add to both targets)
- `macos-client/termihui-client/` — macOS-specific code (PBXFileSystemSynchronizedRootGroup)
- `macos-client/termihui-client-ios/` — iOS-specific code (PBXFileSystemSynchronizedRootGroup)
